answers.body_markdown:
Compared to Win32 applications, UWP applications may be different in the way of saving files.

&gt; I would like to save multiple text box Data in UWP App

I don&#39;t know how you plan to organize the contents of these `TextBox`s, but it&#39;s not difficult. You can use the `TextBox.Text` to get the contents of the text box and combine them the way you want.

&gt; to an external file that can be named every time the file is saved (eg txt file)

I assume that you have organized the text and need to save the text to a local file.

Please note that in UWP apps, you cannot write files directly through the path. You have two ways to get the file:

1. Save the file in `LocalFolder`

```csharp
public async static Task WriteHistory(string content, string fileName)
{
    var localFolder = ApplicationData.Current.LocalFolder;
    var file = await localFolder.CreateFileAsync(fileName, CreationCollisionOption.OpenIfExists);
    await FileIO.WriteTextAsync(file, content);
}
```

2. Open the file you want to save content with `FileOpenPicker`

```csharp
public async static Task&lt;StorageFile&gt; OpenLocalFile(params string[] types)
{
    var picker = new FileOpenPicker();
    picker.SuggestedStartLocation = PickerLocationId.DocumentsLibrary;
    Regex typeReg = new Regex(@&quot;^\.[a-zA-Z0-9]+$&quot;);
    foreach (var type in types)
    {
        if (type == &quot;*&quot; || typeReg.IsMatch(type))
            picker.FileTypeFilter.Add(type);
        else
            throw new InvalidCastException(&quot;Invalid file type&quot;);
    }
    var file = await picker.PickSingleFileAsync();
    return file;
}
```
After that, you can use `await FileIO.WriteTextAsync(file, content);` to write the text to the selected file.

Best regards.

